author: Hiroyuki Kachi
title: USD/JPY Likely to Remain Rangebound, China Trade Balance Eyed
text: [Dow Jones] The USD/JPY will likely remain trapped in a 119.70-120.30 range, during Asia trade, says Akira Moroga, manager of forex products group at Aozora Bank. While resources-related currencies are bought, the USD/JPY pair (now at 120.04) is straightjackted in a tight range, amid receding expectations for the Fed’s rate increase and improved risk sentiment, says Moroga. “It seems the yen is not no so much bought,” he says.
